## CACHING — REDIS ONLY, NO SIGNALR
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

IMPORTANT: There is NO SignalR in this project.
Do not reference Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR anywhere.

Cache strategy: Cache-aside with Redis. TTL = 30 seconds (from config).
SDK polls every 30 seconds → changes reflect within one poll cycle.

Cache key pattern:
  "flagly:flags:{projectId}:{environmentApiKey}" → JSON of full flag list
  "flagly:project:{projectSlug}" → project + environments metadata

IFlagCacheService (Flagly.Infrastructure/Caching/):
  Task<List<FeatureFlagDto>?> GetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task SetFlagsAsync(string cacheKey, List<FeatureFlagDto> flags, TimeSpan ttl);
  Task InvalidateAsync(string cacheKey);
  Task InvalidateByProjectIdAsync(Guid projectId);

RedisFlagCacheService implements IFlagCacheService:
- Use StackExchange.Redis IConnectionMultiplexer
- Serialize with System.Text.Json
- On Redis failure: catch, log with Serilog, return null (fallback to DB)
- InvalidateByProjectIdAsync: SCAN keys matching "flagly:flags:{projectId}:*" → delete all

When a flag or targeting changes:
1. Save to DB
2. Call InvalidateByProjectIdAsync
3. Next SDK poll (≤30s) fetches fresh data → re-caches

