## SDK (Flagly.SDK — classlib in solution)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

FlaglyOptions:
  string ServerUrl
  string ApiKey
  string AppName
  int PollingIntervalSeconds = 30
  bool SendMetrics = true
  bool DefaultWhenUnavailable = false

FlaglyContext:
  string? UserId
  string? UserEmail
  string? SessionId
  Dictionary<string, string> Properties

IFlaglyService:
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName);
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName, string userId);
  bool IsEnabled(string flagName, FlaglyContext context);
  Task RefreshAsync(CancellationToken ct = default);

SDK usage (must work exactly like this):
  // Simple — checks against Everyone or resolves with no user context:
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature")) { }

  // With userId:
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature", currentUser.Id)) { }

  // With full context:
  var ctx = new FlaglyContext { UserId = "u1", UserEmail = "u@co.com" };
  if (flagly.IsEnabled("awesome-feature", ctx)) { }

SDK internals:
- FlaglyBackgroundService : BackgroundService
  - On startup: GET /api/client/features → store in ConcurrentDictionary<string, FeatureFlagDto>
  - Poll every PollingIntervalSeconds
  - On failure: log warning, keep stale cache (fail open/closed per DefaultWhenUnavailable)
- IsEnabled() is synchronous, zero latency — reads from ConcurrentDictionary only
  NEVER make HTTP calls inside IsEnabled()
- GroupMembers are included in the API response DTO so SDK can evaluate client-side
- Metrics: buffer in ConcurrentQueue, flush every 10s via POST /api/client/metrics (batched)
- Auto-inject userId from IHttpContextAccessor if available in DI

Registration:
  builder.Services.AddFlaglySdk(options => {
      options.ServerUrl = config["Flagly:ServerUrl"];
      options.ApiKey = config["Flagly:ApiKey"];
      options.AppName = "my-app";
  });

